agrees with theirs\non the slope as well as on the magnitude of the scatter. As a by-product of the\nnarrowness of the size--mass relation (only 0.06 dex), we propose to use the\nsize of a galaxy to measure its stellar mass. In terms of observing time, it is\nnot more demanding than the usual photometric techniques and may present\npractical advantages in particular cases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Apr 2020 16:39:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-20"}
