ze particles at optical wavelengths.\nThese are among the smallest uncertainties reported to date for an exoplanet,\ndemonstrating both the power and the limitations of HST and Spitzer exoplanet\nobservations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Apr 2020 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 14 May 2020 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 24 Jul 2020 00:30:06 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 30 Jul 2020 23:18:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-19"}
