eneralized to arbitrary\nmetric theories in $D$ dimensions. The results are developed in the framework\nof Lovelock gravity and applied to calculate masses of Schwarzschild-like black\nholes. The bimetric formalism makes it natural to consider a graviton mass.\nBabak and Grishchuk's numerical and hence nonperturbative work sheds light on\nquestions of a (dis)continuous massless limit for massive pure spin-2 and the\nclassical (in)stability of spin-2/spin-0 theory.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Apr 2020 21:59:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-23"}
